Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Protecting the rights of key HIV-affected women and girls in health care settings: A legal scan", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-rights-key-hiv-affected-women-and-girls-health-care-settings-legal-scan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "63b2c9c026b14f98e9b992591406cdf37e4ee2f93b9e0ea2297d7c08ed6f0893"}, "3": {"node_id": "9f605e54-927c-4512-9d3b-12eec6af4185", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-rights-key-hiv-affected-women-and-girls-health-care-settings-legal-scan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "f6c44883bdd02ab4b91c46e7d9295a1d4697b195dcf9e7bb0e48b9cfccbc3ad1"}}, "hash": "49bf8d087b7d5315a590724377a14fc246e585fe3550d97ba8c29ebdc1556365", "text": "Empowered lives. Resilient nations. RegIoNAl RePoRt BANglAdesH, INdIA, PAkIstAN, NePAl PRoteCtINg tHe RIgHts oF key HIV-AFFeCted womeN ANd gIRls IN HeAltH CARe settINgs: A legAl sCAN Proposed citation: UNDP, WAP+, APN+ and SAARCLAW (2013). Protecting the rights of key HIV-affected women and girls in health care settings: A legal scan - Regional report. Bangkok. The views expressed in this publication are those of the authors and do not necessarily represent those of the United Nations, including UNDP, or UN Member States. UNDP partners with people at all levels of society to help build nations that can withstand crisis, and drive and sustain the kind of growth that improves the quality of life for everyone. On the ground in 177 countries and territories, we offer global perspective an