ncerns such as sexually transmitted diseases, in particular HIV/AIDS, and those adversely affecting sexual and reproductive health.\u201d This includes the provision of adequate information including on sexual and reproductive health, which would allow people to make informed decisions with regard to 120 Human Rights Committee, CCPR General Comment", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "6172c2c1-b924-4e88-b691-fed284efaffb": {"__data__": {"id_": "6172c2c1-b924-4e88-b691-fed284efaffb", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-rights-key-hiv-affected-women-and-girls-health-care-settings-legal-scan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Protecting the rights of key HIV-affected women and girls in health care settings: A legal scan", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-rights-key-hiv-affected-women-and-girls-health-care-settings-legal-scan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "0d3eefc39720c1d6f6b3532efbbe1d34c921b47e8ecf466305924fde3a016fc0"}, "3": {"node_id": "96cd8713-8e14-43bd-b9e7-1e1c380fe795", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-rights-key-hiv-affected-women-and-girls-health-care-settings-legal-scan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "c3994c27bdbb6ef5027935340ccbefde5fcbb94fcd3256f533309c2ca1d0ab39"}}, "hash": "e5d30735f36827b26677cd74c38cbc30747c49095