-and-law/current-cases.html. R Rajagopal v. State of T.N., 6 SCC 632. Mr X v. Hospital Z (1998) 8 SCC 296. Naz Foundation (India) Trust v. Government of NCT of Delhi and Others, WP(C)No.7455/2001 [Delhi High Court], Date of Decision: 2 July, 2009. Sunil Babu Pant v. Government of Nepal (2007) at http://njanepal.org.np/Anex_2.pdf. Sapana Pradhan Malla v. Office of Prime Minister and Council of Minister and Others, Writ No. 3561 of the year 2063 B. S (2006). Forum for Women, Law, and Development v. His Majesty\u2019s Government/Nepal . Interrights Written Submission: European Court of Human Rights, Kiyutin v. Russia, Application no. 2700/10. Protecting the rights of key HIV-affected women and girls in health care settings: A legal scan E R United Nations Development Programme UNDP Asia-Pacifi c Regional Centre United Nations Service Building, 3rd Floor Rajdamnern Nok Avenue, Bangkok 10200, Thailand Email: aprc.th@undp.org Tel: +66 (0)2 304-9100 Fax: +66 (0)2 280-2700 Web: http://asia-pacifi c.undp.org/ Empowered lives. Resilient nations. November 2013", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "5a9b9982-ac27-4d65-b9eb-4c9e6192ef72": {"__data__": {"id_": "5a9b9982-ac27-4d65-b9eb-4c9e6192ef72", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/punitive-laws-human-rights-and-hiv-prevention-among-men-who-have-sex-men-asia-pacific-high-level-dialogue-report", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Punitive Laws, Human Rights and HIV prevention among men who have sex with men in Asia Pacific - High Level Dialogue Report", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publicati