 sex with men and transgender people in the Asia-Paci\ufffdc Region\ufffd (2010), and the UNDP \ufffdDeveloping a Comprehensive Package of Services to Reduce HIV among Men who have Sex with Men and Transgender Populations in Asia and the Paci\ufffdc\ufffd (2009). The UNDP-led development process involved input and guidance from a number of people experienced in the delivery of health services to MSM and transgender people including a regional consultation with 36 informal experts from nine countries in Asia convened with support from UNDP, WHO (SEARO and WPRO) and others. The training package had also been extensively piloted in China, Indonesia, the Philippines and Timor-Leste. Malaysia is scheduled to hold a pilot training in October 2013. SESSION 2 STATUS OF PREVENTION, CARE AND TREATMENT FOR MSM AND TRANSGENDER PEOPLE An overview of the HIV epidemic and STI infections among MSM in the Asia-Paci\ufffdc region, including the epidemic and response, \ufffdnancing the response, and the legal environment was provided by UNAIDS.\u00b9\u00b9 There is ample evidence that MSM and transgender people su\ufffder disproportionately from the HIV epidemic. MSM infection rates in countries and cities in the region are shockingly high \ufffd 20 percent in Thailand, 16.7 percent in Vietnam, 31.3 percent in Bangkok, and 17.2 percent in Jakarta. MSM as a \u00b9\u00b9 \ufffdGetting to Zero: Data for action,\ufffd Dr. Vladanka Andreeva, Strategic Intervention Adviser on Prevention and Treatment, UNAIDS RST, Presentation on August 21, 2013, Bangkok, Thailand. 10 Regional Consultation on Improving Access to Prevention, Care and Treatment of HIV among Men who Have Sex with Men and Transgender People proportion of all infections are rising rapidly. In low-income countries in the region, only 14 percent of MSM have access to HIV services. Of the total global AIDS spending of over $1.3 billion, only less than 1 percent ($12 million) is targeted speci\ufffdcally towards MSM. Only 26 percent of the total ($346 million) is earmarked for prevention e\ufffdorts. Addressing the epidemic among MSM in the Asia-Paci\ufffdc region is made even more di\ufffdcult because 18 out of 38 countries criminalize consensual same sex behaviour. Almost all available data on MSM and transgender people is not disaggregated and for the most part only report on HIV trends among the former. There is an urgent need to get more actionable evidence and data on HIV among transgender people. Evidence for Treatment as Prevention (TasP) is based on studies of heterosexual cohorts. The applicability of TasP for MSM needs to be further examined.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "d421c7d1-62f9-4ad3-ac7e-c74481991048": {"__data__": {"id_": "d421c7d1-62f9-4ad3-ac7e-c74481991048", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/regional-consultation-improving-access-prevention-care-and-treatment-hiv-among-men-who-have-sex-men-and-transgender-people", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Regional Consultation on Improving Access to Prevention, Care and Treatment of HIV among Men who have Sex with Men and Transgender People: Meeting Report", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/regional-consultation-improving-access-prevention-care-and-treatment-hiv-among-men-who-have-sex-men-and-transgender-people", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "7942deb667288ae3bfb067f66817955dfafc0138fa774bc49bb6dce0d9a24418"}, "2": {"node_id": "03037f55-f409-46f7-a255-6e1621829ea6", "node_ty